race.comment: FLORAL LEGEND (2) peaks off a near miss here when she led them up. The Sydney-trained mare has more to give and rates to go one better. The local SILVER SERENADE (9) was beaten 1.3L at Moruya on debut from the speed and is sure to improve off that. Draws an inside gate and will get every chance. CHALET (6) debuts for the sharp Baker yard and owns a Randwick trial win. Looks to have good ability, and expect him to be ready to go. The betting will be key. WILL ONE (1) led and missed a whisker at Cootamundra on debut off a big trial win here. Has an awkward gate but McDougall is a key jockey engagement replacing the apprentice. Keep safe.
